// example: userName::uid:gid::"homeDir":"shellExecDir"::permFlags::dirAccess"/System/Boot"ro:"/System/Users/userName"rw:

// permFlags:
/*
r  = read files
w  = write files
x  = execute binaries
s  = shell access
a  = admin privileges (can modify users/system)
m  = mount volumes
n  = network access
d  = device access (e.g., USB, serial)
l  = log access
t  = time management (change system clock)
c  = config access (edit system config files)
b  = boot access (can modify /System/Boot)
u  = user management (add/remove users)

Example: rwxs = read, write, execute, and shell access
*/

